Package org.gservlet.annotation

Contains a number of annotations that allow users to declare servlets, filters, listeners and to specify the metadata for the declared component.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ContextAttributeListener
    This annotation is used to declare a ServletContextAttributeListener.
    ContextListener
    This annotation is used to declare a ServletContextListener.
    Filter
    This annotation is used to declare a Filter.
    InitParam
    This annotation is used on a Servlet or Filter implementation class to specify an initialization parameter.
    RequestAttributeListener
    This annotation is used to declare a ServletRequestAttributeListener.
    RequestListener
    This annotation is used to declare a ServletRequestListener.
    Servlet
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpServlet.
    SessionActivationListener
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpSessionActivationListener.
    SessionAttributeListener
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpSessionAttributeListener.
    SessionBindingListener
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpSessionBindingListener.
    SessionIdListener
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpSessionIdListener.
    SessionListener
    This annotation is used to declare a HttpSessionListener.

Package org.gservlet.annotation Description

Contains a number of annotations that allow users to declare servlets, filters, listeners and to specify the metadata for the declared component.
